        <title>Measures of Center</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>A description of a distribution almost always includes a measure of its center or
            average. The two common measures of center are the <em>mean</em> and the
            <em>median</em>.</p>
        <p>In this exercise, we <!--will use a Java applet-->use an HTML activity to explore the relationship between the mean
            and the median. The activity appears below.</p>
